ENTRY            D0211   20260106   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D0211001   20260106   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 13         38
TITLE      Charge-exchange reaction induced by 6He and nuclear
            densities
AUTHOR     (M.D.Cortina-Gil, A.Pakou, N.Alamanos, W.Mittig,
            P.Roussel-Chomaz, F.Auger, J.Barrette, Y.Blumenfeld,
            J.M.Casandjian, M.Chartier, E.Dietrich,
            V.Fekou-Youmbi, B.Fernandez, N.Frascaria, A.Gillibert,
            H.Laurent, A.Lepine-Szily, N.Orr, V.Pascalon,
            J.A.Scarpaci, J.L.Sida, T.Suomijarvi)
INSTITUTE  (2FR GAN,2FR SAC,1CANMCG,1USALRL,2FR PAR,3BZLUSP,
            2FR CAE,2GRCIOA)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,641,263,1998)
REL-REF    (I,D0245001,M.D.Cortina-Gil+,J,PL/B,371,14,1996)
            Experimental details (sample, detector)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2FR GAN)
INC-SOURCE (FRAGM) C(13C,6He) with 75 MeV/nucleon 13C beam
            on a 1155 mg/cm2 carbon production target.
           The secondary beam was analyzed by the alpha
            spectrometer with a magnetic rigidity set at 2.82 Tm
            which corresponds to an average energy of
            41.6 MeV/nucleon for the 6He ions.
SAMPLE     100 um thick polypropylene foil, (CH2)3.
MONITOR    (3-LI-6(N,P)2-HE-6,,SIG)
           Absolute cross sections were obtained by comparing
            Gamow-Teller transition data with reported data for
            the inverse 6Li(n,p)6He reaction.
MONIT-REF  (13152002,D.Pocanic+,J,CJP,65,687,1987)
           (,J.Rapaport+,J,PR/C,41,1920,1990)
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,IOCH,SCIN) Scattered particles were
            unambiguously identified in the focal plane of the
            spectrometer with an ionisation chamber and a plastic
            scintillater.
           The momentum and scattering angle were measured with
            two position sensitive drift chambers placed 70 cm
            apart and located near the focal plane.
STATUS     (TABLE) Tables received from Valerie Lapoux
           (APRVD) Proofread by Valerie Lapoux (2004-10-13)
HISTORY    (20041004C) SD
           (20260106A) On. Major revision in 002.
ENDBIB              38
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           41
SUBENT        D0211002   20260106   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                  3          5
REACTION   ((1-H-1(2-HE-6,N)3-LI-6,PAR,DA,RSD)=
           (2-HE-6(P,N)3-LI-6,PAR,DA))
ERR-ANALYS (ANG-ERR) Scale error
           (DATA-ERR) Experimental error
HISTORY    (20260106A) On. REACTION corrected.
ENDBIB               5
